description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are seeking an experienced and dynamic Clinical Practice Advanced Practitioner - Level 1 with an independent prescribing qualification to join the Bournemouth West Locality Community Mental Health Team working full time: 37.5 hours per week.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will demonstrate an ability to work independently and as part of the multi-disciplinary team to screen new referrals, provide comprehensive assessments and deliver evidence based interventions, in addition to offering clinical leadership to continue the growth and development of the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are able to offer support and access to the Masters in Advanced Clinical Practice if you do not already have this qualification. Comprehensive clinical supervision and induction will be provided.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Employment in this post requires an Enhanced Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS) check. The DBS levies a charge of £40 and the Trust will recover this cost in instalments from your first 3 salary payments. This will only apply to candidates who are new to the Trust and not internal staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants who subscribe to the DBS update service and are able to present a valid DBS certificate will not incur a charge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Adrian Rendall Job title: Team Leader&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: adrian.rendall1@nhs.net Telephone number: 01202 584440&lt;/p&gt;
